ame":"Gavin Matthews","username":"bovlb","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bovlb/{size}/167232_2.png","created_at":"2024-09-01T21:46:29.139Z","cooked":"<p>If you track the robot’s position during the path (e.g. using the Field2d widget), does it think it’s on the path or does it reflect what the robot is doing?</p>
<p>It’s hard to advise you with knowing more about your system.  Is it possible to share your codebase?</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":20,"updated_at":"2024-09-01T21:46:29.139Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":146,"readers_count":145,"score":49.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":470263,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-following-multiple-paths-does-not-work","display_username":"Gavin Matthews","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":38743,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-following-multiple-paths-does-not-work/470263/4","custom_user_title":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)","reactions":[{"id":"point_up","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3420013,"name":"Will Weiszhaar","username":"trig","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/ebca7d/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-09-01T21:46:55.192Z","cooked":"<p>Could you upload a video of your robot running the auto with the Telemetry panel pulled up? That should show us what is going on under the hood.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":20,"updated_at":"2024-09-01T21:46:55.192Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":139,"readers_count":138,"score":32.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":470263,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-following-multiple-paths-does-not-work","display_username":"Will Weiszhaar","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":65296,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-following-multiple-paths-does-not-work/470263/5","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3420019,"name":"","username":"crazyface","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/67e7ee/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-09-01T21:58:36.999Z","cooked":"<p>I’m not too sure but from what I remember it diverges from the intended path and there is position error. The robot is currently going under some mechanical fixes but I’ll get a for sure answer soon. Here is our code in the meantime: <a href="https://github.com/redlandsrobotics/2024Crescendo.git" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">GitHub - redlandsrobotics/2024Crescendo</a></p>
<p>Thanks for the response!</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":20,"updated_at":"2024-09-01T21:58:36.999Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":133,"readers_count":132,"score":31.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":470263,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-following-multiple-paths-does-not-work","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/redlandsrobotics/2024Crescendo.git","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - redlandsrobotics/2024Crescendo","clicks":5}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":38743,"username":"bovlb","name":"Gavin Matthews","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bovlb/{size}/167232_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63609,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"crazyface"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-following-multiple-paths-does-not-work/470263/6","custom_user_title":"crazyface","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3420020,"name":"","username":"crazyface","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/67e7ee/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-09-01T21:59:58.873Z","cooked":"<p>I’ll upload one soon, but from what I saw on the telemetry it goes off the intended path, and there is a large path inaccuracy starting on the second path.</p>
<p>Thanks for the response!</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":20,"updated_at":"2024-09-01T21:59:58.873Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":130,"readers_count":129,"score":31.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":470263,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-following-multiple-paths-does-not-work","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":65296,"username":"trig","name":"Will Weiszhaar","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/ebca7d/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63609,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"crazyface"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-following-multiple-paths-does-not-work/470263/7","custom_user_title":"crazyface","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3420027,"name":"Will Weiszhaar","username":"trig","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/ebca7d/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-09-01T22:26:00.146Z","cooked":"<p>After looking at your code, I’ve noticed some interesting things that you might want to look at:<br>
First, I wouldn’t leave your translation <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> Constants at 0, so set them to something (the docs has them set to 5.0, 0, 0)</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java"> new HolonomicPathFollowerConfig(
                        new PIDConstants(0.0, 0, 0), // Update This!
                        new PIDConstants(0.5, 1.0 , 0.0), 
                        4.5, // Max module speed, in m/s
                        0.3556, // Drive base radius in meters. Distance from robot center to furthest module.
                        new ReplanningConfig() // Default path replanning config. See the API for the options here
                )
</code></pre>
<p>Next, I noticed that manually add all your autos to your <code>sendableChooser</code>, which isn’t inherently bad, but Pathplanner provides a function to do that automatically. Consider changing your code to remove that potential faliure point:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">public class RobotContainer {
  private final SendableChooser&lt;Command&gt; autoChooser;

  public RobotContainer() {
    // ...

    // Build an auto chooser. This will use Commands.none() as the default option.
    autoChooser = AutoBuilder.buildAutoChooser();

    // Another option that allows you to specify the default auto by its name
    // autoChooser = AutoBuilder.buildAutoChooser("My Default Auto");

    SmartDashboard.putData("Auto Chooser", autoChooser);
  }
</code></pre>
<p>from <a href="https://pathplanner.dev/pplib-build-an-auto.html#create-a-sendablechooser-with-all-autos-in-project" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Build an Auto | PathPlanner Docs</a></p>
<p>Besides this one issue and kinda a QOL feature, I didn’t really find anything else that caught my eye. Try these changes and get back to me.</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":20,"updated_at":"2024-09-01T22:26:00.146Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":126,"readers_count":125,"score":50.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":470263,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-following-multiple-paths-does-not-work","display_username":"Will Weiszhaar","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://pathplanner.dev/pplib-build-an-auto.html#create-a-sendablechooser-with-all-autos-in-project","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Build an Auto | PathPlanner Docs","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":63609,"username":"crazyface","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/67e7ee/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":65296,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-following-multiple-paths-does-not-work/470263/8","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"point_up","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3420028,"name":"","username":"crazyface","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/67e7ee/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-09-01T22:29:56.838Z","cooked":"<p>Thanks a lot! I’ll add those changes. Will get back to you! <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/pray.png?v=12" title=":pray:" class="emoji" alt=":pray:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":20,"updated_at":"2024-09-01T22:29:56.838Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":106,"readers_count":105,"score":41.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":470263,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-following-multiple-paths-does-not-work","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":65296,"username":"trig","name":"Will Weiszhaar","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/ebca7d/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63609,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"crazyface"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-following-multiple-paths-does-not-work/470263/9","custom_user_title":"crazyface","reactions":[{"id":"hugs","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3420032,"name":"Gavin Matthews","username":"bovlb","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bovlb/{size}/167232_2.png","created_at":"2024-09-01T22:46:28.623Z","cooked":"<p>I agree with both of those, especially the <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> constants.</p>
<p>I also noticed that the co-ordinates used in <a href="https://github.com/redlandsrobotics/2024Crescendo/blob/7f6a86cd6de71df8f75bd1d3fb1c6ca10a34e753/src/main/java/frc/robot/Constants.java#L39C47-L39C63" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">kDriveKinematics</a> don’t seem to match up.  Everywhere else your module order is FL/FR/BL/BR, but here it is BR/BL/FR/FL.   See <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/basic-programming/coordinate-system.html#wpilib-coordinate-system" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">WPILib coordinate system</a>.</p>
<p>Finally, a minor point, but I recommend you get rid of <code>DriveStation.getHeading</code>, and instead implement <code>getRotation2d</code> using <code>ADXRS450_Gyro.getRotation2d</code>.</p>","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"posts_count":20,"updated_at":"2024-09-01T22:46:28.623Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":106,"readers_count":105,"score":36.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":470263,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-following-multiple-paths-does-not-work","display_username":"Gavin Matthews","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/basic-programming/coordinate-system.html#wpilib-coordinate-system","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Coordinate System — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":2},{"url":"https://github.com/redlandsrobotics/2024Crescendo/blob/7f6a86cd6de71df8f75bd1d3fb1c6ca10a34e753/src/main/java/frc/robot/Constants.java#L39C47-L39C63","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"2024Crescendo/src/main/java/frc/robot/Constants.java at 7f6a86cd6de71df8f75bd1d3fb1c6ca10a34e753 · redlandsrobotics/2024Crescendo · GitHub","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":65296,"username":"trig","name":"Will Weiszhaar","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/ebca7d/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":38743,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-following-multiple-paths-does-not-work/470263/10","custom_user_titl